The paper deals with a multi-agent resource allocation problem, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves finding a welfare-achieving allocation, which requires optimization techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves constraints and fairness considerations, which are relevant topics in optimization (cs.DS) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
